From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|pur||lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|pur||lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|purus||clean, free from dirt or filth, unmixed, plain|lang=la}}, from Proto-Indo-European {{m|ine-pro|*peu-}}, {{m|ine-pro|*pu-||to cleanse, purify}}. Displaced native [[Middle English]] {{term|lutter||pure, clear, sincere|lang=enm}} (from [[Old English]] {{m|ang|hlūtor}}, {{term|hluttor||lang=ang}}), [[Middle English]] {{term|skere||pure, sheer, clear|lang=enm}} (from [[Old English]] {{m|ang|scǣre}} and Old Norse {{term|skǣr||lang=non}}), [[Middle English]] {{term|schir||clear, pure|lang=enm}} (from [[Old English]] {{m|ang|scīr}}), [[Middle English]] {{term|smete|smete, smeate|pure, refined|lang=enm}} (from [[Old English]] {{m|ang|smǣte}}; compare [[Old English]] {{m|ang|mǣre||pure}}).

